MIME media type name : Application

MIME subtype name : Vendor Tree - vnd.eudora.data

Required parameters : None.

Optional parameters :
Private parameters defined internally by QUALCOMM for Eudora only.

Encoding considerations :
7Bit. Data is treated as US-ASCII with text (i.e., CRLF)
canonicalization.

Security considerations :
This data is interpreted and used by the Eudora e-mail client. Some
data may cause operational changes in Eudora, and hence some security issues
may arise. However, since both the data format itself and the
operational changes are private to Eudora, there should be no impact on other
applications (who should ignore all data of this MIME type).

Interoperability considerations :
Private use only to Eudora.

Published specification :
None.

Applications which use this media :
Eudora version 4.3 and later.
